{"_id":"5c098280-87f0-11eb-a855-5582c59c7d03","postId":"2020_03_valuetask-b9bb171a-f89c-302e-8f06-64dd691d79fc","postUri":"https://blog.stephencleary.com/2020/03/valuetask.html","replyTo":"e06c95a0-763c-11eb-9c6c-ed0d94f8c29c","authorEmailEncrypted":"","authorEmailMD5":"23448e78d187fba56d8bc263081ac5d8","authorName":"Stephen Cleary","authorUri":"https://stephencleary.com","message":"I mean that if you want *any* of these:\r\n\r\n- `await` more than once.\r\n- `Task.WhenAll`\r\n- `Task.WhenAny`\r\n\r\nThen you should call `AsTask` once and then use the task from then on. You can't pass a `ValueTask<T>` to `Task.WhenAll` at all; the code won't compile.","date":"2021-03-18T13:46:37.281Z"}